# Slack Block Kit Builder

> **Package Type**: Python Library  
> **Primary Use**: Slack Block Kit JSON Generation  
> **Pattern**: Builder Pattern with Method Chaining  
> **Validation**: Pydantic-based Type Safety  
> **Target**: Slack API Integration  

A comprehensive Python package for building Slack Block Kit structures with dedicated classes using the builder pattern. Provides a type-safe, intuitive API for creating Slack messages, modals, and home tabs without the complexity of raw JSON construction.

## ğŸ“‹ Quick Reference

**Main Classes:**
- `Message` - Build Slack messages with blocks
- `Modal` - Build interactive modals  
- `HomeTab` - Build home tab interfaces
- `Section`, `Actions`, `Context` - Block containers
- `Button`, `SelectMenu`, `Input` - Interactive elements
- `PlainText`, `MrkdwnText` - Text objects

**Key Methods:**
- `.create()` - Initialize objects
- `.build()` - Generate JSON output
- `.add_*()` - Add blocks/elements (Message builder)
- `.set_*()` - Configure properties (Builder pattern)

### ğŸ¤– AI Agent Decision Tree

**Need to create a Slack message?**
```
Start with Message.create()
â”œâ”€â”€ Add text content? â†’ .add_section(text)
â”œâ”€â”€ Add interactive buttons? â†’ .add_actions([Button.create(text, action_id)])
â”œâ”€â”€ Add form inputs? â†’ .add_input(label, InputElement.create(action_id))
â”œâ”€â”€ Add images? â†’ .add_image(url, alt_text)
â””â”€â”€ Add context info? â†’ .add_context([text_or_elements])
```

**Need interactive elements?**
```
Button â†’ Button.create(text, action_id)
Dropdown â†’ StaticSelect.create(action_id, placeholder, options)
Text Input â†’ PlainTextInput.create(action_id)
Date Picker â†’ DatePicker.create(action_id)
Multi-select â†’ MultiStaticSelect.create(action_id, placeholder, options)
```

**Need text formatting?**
```
Plain text â†’ PlainText.create(text)
Markdown â†’ MrkdwnText.create(text)
```

**Need a modal?**
```
Start with Modal.create(title)
â”œâ”€â”€ Add inputs â†’ .add_input(label, element)
â”œâ”€â”€ Set buttons â†’ .submit(text).close(text)
â””â”€â”€ Add metadata â†’ .callback_id(id).private_metadata(data)
```

## ğŸš€ Features

- **ğŸ—ï¸ Builder Pattern**: Fluent method chaining for intuitive API design
- **ğŸ”’ Type Safety**: Full pydantic validation with comprehensive type hints
- **ğŸ“¦ Complete Coverage**: All Slack Block Kit blocks, elements, and composition objects
- **ğŸ”„ Easy Migration**: Clear 1:1 mapping to Slack Block Kit JSON structure
- **âœ¨ Code Quality**: Ruff linting, mypy type checking, comprehensive test coverage
- **ğŸ“š Rich Documentation**: Extensive examples, API reference, and migration guides
- **âš¡ Performance**: Optimized for both development and production use

